President Obama has nominated Stephanie Dawn Thacker to serve on the United States Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit. Thacker is currently a partner at the law firm of Guthrie & Thomas PLLC, specializing in complex litigation, environmental and toxic tort litigation, and criminal defense. She also teaches as an adjunct professor at the West Virginia University School of Law. Thacker has a background in both private practice and public service, having worked at the United States Attorney's Office for the Southern District of West Virginia and the Child Exploitation and Obscenity Section of the United States Department of Justice. She has received several awards for her work, including the Attorney General's Distinguished Service Award. Thacker joined Guthrie & Thomas in 2006.